commit.message:
Revert "Fix typos in *.dtd files".  It changed some of the enums.  Typos or not, it's part of the standard, and will break stuff that use it.  The dtd files are suppoesed to be those published with the standard, unmodified.

This reverts commit 3d50f6bd70b29b049997d41471751f334109868a.

configure.ac: Fix issues detected with autoupdate

Remove obsolete macros and use replacements where needed; fix the usage
of AC_CONFIG_FILES and AC_OUTPUT. Also fix the description of HAVE_ICONV.

Define HAVE_LIBCURL when using Autoconf

Even if libcurl was available, the conditional code for ofxconnect
that uses libcurl was not compiled, so that it was not possible to
connect to an OFX server. (Also, correct a misspelling of "libofx"
in the error message that was returned instead.)

Fixes: 1b9e698000a2 ("Remove hand-written libcurl configure check,
                      use pkg-config instead.")

Remove handling for obsolete partner server

The parter server was shut down 10 years ago; FI settings must now
be entered manually. Remove this code to avoid confusion.

Closes: #6
Remove comparison of int and bool by evaluating the int in the if-clause directly
libofx is now upstream in vcpkg; add relevant docs
Version bump 0.10.9
Add NEWS for upcoming 0.10.9

Fix library name on Windows

Fixes #88

Fix several more memory issues (#90)

* Fix another downcast in ofx_container_account.cpp
* Fix errant read from heap
* Avoid deleting 'this' in OfxMainContainer
* Add test cases for memory issues

Fix installation path of libofx.h (#83)

Install libofx.h as <includedir>/libofx/libofx.h as in version 10.0.5.
Currently, it's installed as <includedir>/libofx.h which breaks the
build of kmymoney and probably every other user of libofx. I guess this
was changed unintentionally with using GNUInstallDirs in
8a154a014962d5ea8ac1c9b59f388013c2e184bb.

Closes: https://github.com/libofx/libofx/issues/76
Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>

CMake: miscellaneous fixes (#73)

* CMake: cleanup whitespace

* CMake: fix version (0.10.5 -> 0.10.6)

* CMake: use GNUInstallDirs

This works fine on Windows too and other non-Linux platforms, despite
the name.

* CMake: install library with -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON and set SONAME

Otherwise, we end up installing tools which were dynamically
linked against libofx.so but they can't find that library.

* CMake: add TODO re docs, tests
